FBIS3-53523 "drnes011_k_94006" FBIS-NES-94-011 Document Type:Daily Report 18 Jan 1994 IRAQ Clashes Between State, Resistance Forces Reported Saddam Forces Ambushed in al-Basrah NC1401163694 (Clandestine) Voice of Iraqi Islamic Revolution in Arabic 1430 GMT 14 Jan 94 NC1401163694 (Clandestine) Voice of Iraqi Islamic Revolution in Arabic 1430 GMT 14 Jan 94 Language: Arabic Article Type:BFN [Text] After observing and monitoring the movements of Saddam's security forces in al-Basrah Governorate, the Islamic resistance forces last week set up ambushes on the road between the district of (al-Mdaynah) and the area of (al-Nasri) which belong to the Governorate of al-Basrah. Our sources affirmed that the resistance ambushes opened fire when the tyrant's security forces passed the above-mentioned road. They said that a fierce battle ensued between the resistance groups and the regime's security forces. A number of soldiers and officers from the tyrant's security forces were killed and the rest withdrew, dragging their tails behind them. The Islamic resistance forces returned to their bases safely.
